As HYDRAS and the other Predacons fly, crawl and walk towards the
co-ordinates sent by LEO PRIME, the Maximals also make their way to
the same location.

Night is begining to set in, the sun dipping behind the horizon, the
light slowly fading from the skies, the moon already making its
presence felt as it loomed on the opposing horizon, large and full,
seemingly ominous in the fading light.

HYDRAS and his team are the first to make it to the site, but only
just bearly. In the distance the Maximal ship also made its way to the
location as well, it's boosters lighting up the swiftly darkning
skies. It is only a few moments before it also arrives and lands, its
landing thrusters blowing aside vegatation and debris and its landing
gear desends.

The area is open all the way around and it is situated at the top of a
hill, one that allows anyone standing upon it the ability to see
anyone coming from any direction. The Maximal ship has landed on the
far side of that hill, a ramp extends, allowing the Maximals to
disembark shold they choose to do so.

(TAG)
